"xylem","5","___ is one of the two types of transport tissue in vascular plants, phloem being the other. The basic function of ___ is to transport water from roots to stems and leaves, but it also transports  nutrients.","wiki"),("syrup","5","In cooking, a ___ or sirup  groups.","wiki"),("flues","5","In some countries, wood fire ___ are often built into a heat preserving construction within which the flue gases circulate over heat retaining bricks before release to the atmosphere. The heat retaining bricks are covered in a decorative material such as brick, tiles or stone. This flue gas circulation avoids the considerable heat loss to the chimney and outside air in conventional systems. The heat from the flue gases is absorbed quickly by the bricks and then released slowly to the house rather than the chimney. In a well insulated home, a single load fire burning for one and a half hours twice a day is enough to keep an entire home warm for a 24-hour period. In this way, less fuel is used, and noxious emissions are reduced. Sometimes, the flue incorporates a second combustion chamber where combustibles in the flue gas are burnt a second time, reducing soot, noxious emissions and increasing overall efficiency.","wiki"),("fruit","5","In botany, a ___ is the seed-bearing structure in flowering plants  formed from the ovary after flowering.","wiki"),("appam","5","Vir Sanghvi, an Indian journalist, quotes food historian K. T. Achaya and states that the ___ is mentioned in the Tamil Perumpanuru. K. T. Achaya in the last published book of his lifetime states that ___ was well established in ancient Tamil country.","wiki"),("blini","5","A ___  buckwheat flour and served with smetana, tvorog, butter, caviar and other garnishes. ___ are among the most popular and most-eaten dishes in Russia.","wiki"),("boxty","5","The most popular version of the dish consists of finely grated raw potato and mashed potato with flour, baking soda, buttermilk, and sometimes egg. The grated potato